Issues.Title: Windows Automation: incorrect tree navigation for Table object.
Issues.Body:
### .NET version

8.0

### Did it work in .NET Framework?

No

### Did it work in any of the earlier releases of .NET Core or .NET 5+?

No

### Issue description

I have a UIA-grid object in which an ITableProvider is applied. The grid has 1 row and 3 columns (3 cells in total). Using the "Accessibility Insights for Windows" application I am trying to check each cell object by hovering over it with the mouse on a form. For cells in columns 2 and 3 everything works, but for cells in column 1 it does not work, why?

### Steps to reproduce

1. Run attached app:
[UiaTableProviderTest.zip](https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/files/12804822/UiaTableProviderTest.zip)
2. Choose one of 4 startup projects (each of the projects meets the .net version).
3. Run "Accessibility Insights for Windows" (AIW) app.
4. Move the mouse pointer under each label, but not over the labels.
5. In AIW app you can see each selected cell corresponding to the UIA-object and its properties (correct), except for cell [0,0] (incorrect).
Issues.RelatedDescription: Open issue "Windows Automation: incorrect tree navigation for Table object." (#10045)
